Let&rsquo;s add rotation to the bird:
Add below command in the file [File: update-game.js] if (bird.angle &lt; 50) { bird.angle += 1; }
Comments: If is a conditional block where we are checking the angle of the bird and if it&rsquo;s less than 50 we are executing the condition. -bird.angle+=1;
Working Together In the repl.it window below, we started the code with the line bird.angle +=1;.
In your console you should see a Jsappy bird rotating with an angle after you press run:

